premise_source_doc_sentence: In 1803 , Abel Jacob Gerhard Seyler sold the pharmacy to Johann Ludewig Wilhelm Gruner , with a ducal privilege from George III .
As Jäger became canonicus at Braunschweig , he sold the pharmacy to Johann Andreae in 1645 with permission from the Duke .
The pharmacy quickly came to serve the ducal court and became the official court pharmacy .

When Ernest Augustus relocated to Hanover in 1680 , Jäger moved his pharmacy as well and demanded the status of court pharmacist and that the Andreae Pharmacy be closed because he claimed to be the `` true court pharmacist . ''
Andreae & Co.  (  informally the Andreasche Apotheke or Andreae Pharmacy  )  was the first court pharmacy in Hanover and was owned by members of the Andreae family from 1645 to 1803 .
